      "side": 1,
      "message": "i am not sure this type is needed. it currently serves two functions:\n\n1) provide indexPoint to collect(). However, all index points from the same workItem are same, and workItem already has indexPoint. We could simplify by replacing `chan chan PageItem` with `chan *workItem`. Then in fetchAll(), for any result we would know the timestamp\n\n2) store offset. However, fetchAll() doesn\u0027t actually send offset. collect() produces offset, but stores it in the PageItem for some reason, as opposed to storing it in a local variable. Also note that it needs offset only of the latest or current item. I think all we need is an int variable there.\n\nfinally, if PageItem doesn\u0027t exist, then we don\u0027t need worker.go:97 loop",
